<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in Argentina (
                        Braden
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v09</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d405</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">405</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-06-21T18:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-06-21T18:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-21T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-21T18:00:00-05:00" n="405" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Argentina/6–2145:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-21T20:00:00-03:00">June 21, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1311. Ref Rio tel. June 21, 1 p.m.<note n="76" xml:id="d405fn76">No. 1977, not
                        printed.</note> Entire fats and oil deal was clarified by recent public
                    statement of Acting Secretary<note n="77" xml:id="d405fn77">Released to the
                        press on June 15; for text, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi> June 17, 1945, p. 1116.</note> and as a matter of fact
                    insufficient Argentine tanker tonnage must be supplemented by us to carry out
                    our part of the agreement to supply fuel oil enabling Argentina to release
                    vegetable oils urgently needed by United Nations.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Rio.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Braden</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
